The paper focuses on the interface design and user perceptions of mobile money applications in Latin America, which suggests a strong emphasis on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the technological requirements and adoption rates of mobile money in developing countries, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes recommendations for future mobile money application design, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
